{{No footnotes|date=October 2015}}
'''Shani Diluka''' (born 7 November 1976 in [[Monaco]]) is a pianist of [[Sri Lanka]]n parents. She was among those to benefit from a programme initiated by [[Princess Grace]] of Monaco, which allowed talented children to receive special music lessons integrated into their normal schooling. She received the first prize in the Académie de Musique (Fondation Prince Rainier III). She subsequently studied with Odile Poisson, a pupil of [[Pierre Sancan]]. Enrolled in the [[Conservatoire de Paris]] in 1997, she studied with [[Georges Pludermacher]] and [[François-Frédéric Guy]] and later with [[Marie-Françoise Bucquet]], [[Nicholas Angelich]] and [[Bruno Rigutto]]
== References == {{Reflist}} * [http://www.shanidiluka.com/main_en.html Diluka's Biography at her website] * [http://www.pianobleu.com/shani_diluka.html Diluka's biography on Piano Bleu]
== External links == * [http://shanidiluka.com/blog/ Shani Diluka's blog]
