{{Use British English|date=August 2012}} {{Use dmy dates|date=August 2012}} {{Infobox person | name = Tanay Chheda
| native_name = | image = Tanay Chheda (cropped).jpg | caption = Tanay Chheda in 2011 | birth_name =Tanay Hemant Chheda | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1996|6|27|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Mumbai]], Maharashtra, India | spouse = | occupation = Actor | children = | education= USC School of Cinematic Arts | years_active = 2006–present }} '''Tanay Hemant Chheda''' (born 27 June 1996) is an [[India]]n actor. He is best known for his child performances in the critically acclaimed films ''[[Taare Zameen Par]]'' (2007) and ''[[Slumdog Millionaire]]'' (2008), with the latter earning him the [[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Cast in a Motion Picture]] and a nomination for Best Ensemble at the [[Black Reel Awards of 2008]].
==Early life and education== Chheda is a [[Gujaratis|Gujarati]] [[Jainism in Gujarat|Jain]] with roots in [[Mandvi]], [[Kutch]] who was born in [[Mumbai]], India, where he currently lives.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/ahmedabad/Young-Slumdog-hails-from-Kutch/articleshow/4039554.cms|title=Young 'Slumdog' hails from Kutch|first=Ankur|last=Jain|publisher=[[Times of India]]|location=[[Ahmedabad]]|date=January 28, 2009}}</ref> He used to study in [[Campion School, Mumbai|Campion School]], but changed to [[Dhirubhai Ambani International School]]; both in Mumbai. He attended the prestigious [[Choate Rosemary Hall]] in Wallingford, Connecticut, US. He is currently in his second year at the USC School of Cinematic Arts.<ref name="Abramovitch Bushan 2014">{{cite web | last=Abramovitch | first=Seth | last2=Bushan | first2=Nyay | title='Slumdog Millionaire' Kids Reunite, Five Years Later: How They're Doing | website=The Hollywood Reporter | date=2014-02-27 | url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/slumdog-millionaire-kids-reunite-five-683120 | accessdate=2016-10-16}}</ref>
==Film career== {{Update|section|inaccurate=y|date=September 2012}} He was first seen in the movie ''[[Don: The Chase Begins Again|Don]]'' in 2006. He has the critically acclaimed ''[[Taare Zameen Par (Like Stars on Earth)]]'' in 2007 to his name and the award-sweeping ''[[Slumdog Millionaire]]'' in 2008.
In ''Don'', he played the role of Deepu, the son of Jasjit (played by [[Arjun Rampal]]) . In ''Taare Zameen Par'', he played the role of a handicapped child who is an extremely helpful and supportive friend to the protagonist Ishaan (played by [[Darsheel Safary]]). In ''Slumdog Millionaire'', Chheda played the role of [[Jamal Malik (character)|Jamal Malik]], in adolescence, for which he has won the [[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Cast in a Motion Picture]] and received a nomination for Best Ensemble at the [[Black Reel Awards of 2008]]. He portrayed the young Rizwan Khan, an [[Autism|autistic]] child, in [[Shahrukh Khan]]'s film, ''[[My Name Is Khan]]''. He was nominated for the best child actor in Star Screen Awards for ''My Name Is Khan''.
He was last seen in a German film ''[[Lilly the Witch: The Journey to Mandolan|Hexe Lilli- Journey to Mandolan]]'' (2011).
